text:
Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

How could the United States have been the only one to follow the isolation. Didnt all the other countries agree to it? Why was the plan not followed through with? 

The answer to that question lies in the fact that the United States was the only nation to have a nuclear bomb. The other nations were afraid that if they went into isolation, the United States would use the bomb on them. The United States, on the other hand, was afraid that if they didnt go into isolation, the other nations would use the bomb on them.  The United States, in order to prevent the other nations from using the bomb on them, decided to use the bomb on them first. The first nuclear bomb to have been dropped on a country that was capable of taking out the entire country. So maybe it was out of ill will and being frustrated that the other nations didnt follow along with the agreement, and just like that the first nuclear war began. 

The nuclear power of the united states was unmatched and much more powerful in comparison to the other nations. The other parts of the world planned on using those fifty years to group together and make nuclear weapons as good as those from the US. They were not able to successfully do so because of issues gathering relevant powerful ingredients. The United States, on the other hand, had no such issues. In fact, the US had a nuclear bomb created long before the isolation even began. This bomb was able to be used to destroy all of russia and one shot. The U.S. could literally wipe whatever country it wanted to out and off the globe. Once that other countries found out about the power of the US, everyone wanted to be their ally now instead. Maybe it was karma.
